reviews.text: Well worth a visit. A must for every resident of Culver City. Traces the history from its beginning and has photos of many “old friend “ businesses. Bring your kids.
Very interesting place to visit to learn about Culver City.

What a great wealth of information about Culver City! The people are friendly and passionate about the history of their town. I love the old signal light from MGM studios, the photos on the walls, the screen-used costumes and all the reference materials available.

Everyone who lives in Culver City should visit the "ARC" (Archives & Resource Center) and talk to the volunteers. I'm looking forward to some tours and other programs by the Society.
I love. Culver City I was raised in the Mar Vista. Gardens housing projects. My name is Diana Olivas b.k.a Droopy 1Culver City mvg little locas!!!

You will not want to miss a trip to the museum. Set aside a few hours. There is so much to see and feel. There are historical tangibles that are sacred and kept safe here. I was changed after a tour. Lloyd was so generous and knowledgeable. A real treasure.

This place is truly a gem, and I'm very surprised more people don't know about it. There is a treasure of civil rights movement archival material here, from print over sound to video, huge music archive, the place can be rented for film shoots, and on specific Sundays there are live jazz performances with amazing musicians.

This Venue is Amazing!  It has rare /out of print books like the Original ...12 Years a Slave, the First published book by Phyllis Wheatley, Slave journals/letters, newspapers, films, movie posters...so Much!  A Library, Musuem, old prison cells!  A virtual TREASURE TROVE OF AMERICAN HISTORY.  MY SOUL WAS ENRICHED!

this is a wonderful cultural resource with an amazing collection | they are always putting on a wide variety of interesting programming that will appeal to multi-generational audiences | the staff and volunteers are so friendly | very well run | it is centrally located and easy to find

Lots of great art and African American historical photos and documents. Excellent place to host an event; they have a stage for music. We came here for a political fundraiser and saw Aloe Blacc and Ganda Boys perform. Don't miss this cultural gem!

From what I could tell this is a small one room gallery with an attached library. I came for an exhibit on mining land use. Unfortunately, if was just a lot of pictures of mines from Google Earth. I learned nothing. Admittedly,, this was my third museum that day and fatigue had set in so there may be more to this place that i just missed.
On weekends you can park in the parking lot of the printing office just across the street to the west as this business is closed on the weekend. They did open 15 min later than advertised.
Quirktastic land use micro-gallery.

Well-curated art and artifact collection reflecting world cultures of the Cold War within a modern space.  Concise, orderly, and thoroughly educational.  Knowledgeable docent was there to show us highlights and give talks of what’s shown. Courteous staff. Be amazed, then take home a bit of history with something from their gift shop.  Good location, good parking.

Great museum. The space is nice and small enough to tour in an hour or two. The free tour gives a nice sampling of the collection. Our tour guide Julia did an excellent job and I learned a lot. Exhibits also rotate every few months so there’s always more to see.
Really interesting! Wish there was more artifacts to look at but still worth the visit. Awesome architecture!

Cold war 1947~1991.
Can't see, talk, think. 
Everything is drab and gray but not interior design, is colorful and modern. 
PS. I didn't know dogs was gone to space?!
Wonderful place to visit and learn about the history of Germany and Russia during the Cold War
Loved this place from the first taste. I had a brother come into town and asked me to take him back here. The bill was decent for the quality.

never been to Indian myself I don't know if this is authentic or not but the place is full of people who obviously hail from or related to those who hail from South Asia subcontinent. Unpretentious flavorful inexpensive and delivered relatively quickly in an unpretentious almost Spartan mini mall atmosphere. The flat screen with TV with the obligatory Bollywood movie is on behind you but mercifully the sound was off. This is a favorite of acquaintances so we come hear three or four  times a year and consistently flavorful. also quite a relief for those who prefer not to eat animals as I believe every item on the list is vegetarian or vegan
These dosas are off the hook! Fantastic Indian cuisine, good buffet and the staff was helpful and understanding guiding us through this tasty experience. Tastes authentic.
Price is reasonable but the quality of food is poor. Sambar was not fresh. I felt that the food was not fresh,it was stale.

They've stopped making some dishes and yet  its still on their menu.  It's frustrating after you nail it down to the single dish and the waiter comes and tells you unapologetically that they don't serve it anymore, and it's been a long time since they stopped serving it. Either print a new menu or cross it out. Its happened on three separate occasions. I've gone there with different people and didn't want to be rude to them thinking they might have printed a new menu but they haven't. This time I complained  and hope someone else doesn't have to go through the same ordeal as I have. Food was fantastic that's why I keep going there but the one star is for waisting my precious time.

Correct me if I'm wrong, I understand the only meat use at this location is ground beef, isn't it? If what I just mentioned is the only kind of tacos they offer at Tito's Tacos (ground beef), I don't want to eat tacos there. I have to admit most people like their tacos so, congrats on it. I honestly grew up eating the real deal though everyone is entitled to their own version. I will eat Tito's Tacos any time I'm with a group of people choosing to go to Tito's but it would never be my first choice. That being said; Tito's Tacos has a great environment and nothing but the best employees at this place. Happy employees makes for HAPPY CUSTOMERS. Tito's Tacos has the best customer experience because of EMPLOYEES. All of this is my own perspective of the place. When I go there or when I pass by there, I can see tons of people enjoying the food at Tito's Tacos. I love seeing the great success they have. Whether ground beef tacos are my first choice or not, makes no difference. What's important is the successful environment delighting hundreds of people everyday. Five stars for Tito's Tacos all the way.

Tito's Tacos is a taco joint that's perfect for a quick dinner run. If you've seen the commercial on TV, their jingle is probably stuck in your head too. There is a lot of debate about the tacos. Some people prefer the meat, others don't like the preparation. My review in particular is about the chips and salsa. It's a win-win for anyone who loves light chips with flavorful salsa. The salsa is also used on other items on the menu and it's SUPER good. If you do order anything here - make sure you get a side of chips and salsa to enjoy too. Now my opinion on the tacos? This item is good! Would I stand in line for the tacos? No, but I do for the chips, salsa and the burritos as it's worth it!

This is the greatest place on Earth!

others try to be as great as Tito's however there will never ever be another restaurant as greatest Tito's Tacos!
Their prices are extremely reasonable and the food has been great all of my life. 
I recommend the burrito made with beans, cheese, lettuce, rice, and onions!
buy some of their extra red salsa because it's worth it to put on their chips and put on every bite of your burrito, and sample everything because it's all good there!

Titos Forever!

It's good, but not 5 stars. Tacos are a crunchy treat. Lots of cheese on the tacos is excellent. Beans are splendid indeed. Rice was bland and dry. Salsa was water and looked cheap, taste was fine. Generous amount of chips. Soda not ridiculously overpriced.

Biggest cons, hard to find a seat. No way to get refill on drink, too busy. A little too expensive.

A solid taco/burrito joint in Culver. The usual choices in Mexican fare but with a distinct flavor--almost homemade style. Burritos are gigantic, tacos are satisfying and you get tons of chips and salsa. You can't go wrong. Lots of good food for not a lot of money. I keep going back over and over.

Too Many Problems just for Simple Mid Eastern food. But, I spoke with the General Manager about them, and he assured Me, that Moving forward, there will be alot of rewarding changes within the Restaurant and Menu... and that he is doing everything in his Power to correct the Customer Service culture of things, in turn the food will have a better effect and atmosphere as well... Good job Amine! 👍🏼 And Thanks for the REFUND. 😉

Their waiting times for food delivery services are unacceptable. Saw at least 5 customers dining in get their food before my order and they got there after. If they change in the future I'll consider switching the rating.

I love all the Gaby's locations, but this one especially is great. They just gave me a drink while I am waiting for my food to-go! Figured the least I could do is leave a review after all the times I've eaten here. Lots of reasonably healthy options - I especially like their creamed spinach. Good for dipping with pita ;) Thanks guys!

Food is always good! They have a VIP reward program that gives you 1 free chicken shwarma for every five visits. My boyfriend and I visited Gaby's on a rainy day and they served everybody a hot soup on the house! Staff is efficient and friendly! It is our usual spot and we usually visit once a week, highly recommend if you want a quality and fast Mediterranean meal.

The manager or owner was very kind.The employees are awesome! Fresh food and reasonable prices.i had a problem only one time on an order larger than my normal.I became very upset with the treatment from the employee's, until I spoke with the owner he offered me one free meal with one purchased.Only thing is I didn't use it right away. When trying to use it three weeks later, no one could find the offer🙄nor remember oh well I had to let it go. I'm still a customer to this day!
L❤VE me some Gaby's!!!
3/1/19 Today I've been trying to place an online order for a hour, today you lost me as a long time customer!
vegan food, yeah, very delicious. I often meet people here to talk. I look forward to a return visit. This place has a cool feel to it. Ambience reminds me of Colorado Springs area.

A total safe haven for plant-based people. Feels like a commune. No frills vegan Indian restaurant with all-you-can-eat buffet for $8. Tons of veggies, leafy greens and gluten free foods. We dined in due to heavy rain. Can't wait to sit on their front patio and enjoy their baked goods with a beverage.
Great location for quality Vegan food. Got there near seven, it wasn't very crowded. The service was very welcoming and observant.
Good location for vegan food. The service here is above par. The bill was good for how much you get. Menu is similar to a restaurant in El Paso I liked.
My fav location for delicious Vegan food. Went there on a Saturday. The place has a good atmosphere.
One of the best menus on the westside. Fresh, well prepared ingredients.  One of my favorite stops anytime of day. Don't forget to try the almond croissants with your coffee.
They made my order perfect! Love their fruit tarts. Highly suggest you get a double cheese burger with bacon!!!
Great food and great atmosphere. With awesome prices. Awesome spot for brunch and a nice morning stroll.

I loved the food, the crepe my sister ordered was delicious. Their French baguette is amazing as well! There’s room for improvement on their service, but it was not a dealbreaker for me. I would come back again!

Service was Horrible!! Food was great. I'm in a wheelchair and it took one waitress and 3 bus boys to to understand that I couldn't sit at the table the way they wanted me to. The customer isn't ways right but the customer does know how their wheelchair works!

I had the Pho Wonton; and enjoyed it. It was fresh tasting and plentiful. However, my server neglected to provide a spoon for my Pho as well as the beansprout, peppers and spice add-in dish. An odd oversight for a Pho restaurant that was easily rectified. 

Seating was tight but not cramped. Tables and chairs are plain wood but comfortable, and the ambiance is warm.

The serving of the food is small and the service was ok. We were given a dirty plate to use for our entree. When I informed the waitress, she was not apologetic at all. The quality of the food is average, I do not recommend this establishment unless you have no other choice
My honey and I love eating here. The owner Robert has a wonderful personality  as well as Jesse an d Tabitha. Wonderful place to dine at
My parents love this place.  So being a good son I tried it for myself and was quite surprised at how yummy the pho was. The house beer IPA was yummy.  I would come in just for the beer 😉.
It can get busy but that's only because it has a great selection of very flavorful food. The place is very spacious and elegant.

Unlike my husband I like this place. Pizza has very thin crust and it's tasty. Their pasta is good too and they have a variety of sweets for desert including icecream. Public parking is near by. They have a large terrace as well as a large airy dinning room. A bit pricey...
Feels like you're in Italy here. One of my favorite spots. Try any pizza. They're all good. Their breakfast is marvelous too. Highly recommend.
Amazing pizza.  Excellent service.  Pastas were good to excellent.  Lasagna just ok.  Gnocchi with Pesto was great.
Unbelievably good Italian restaurant. There is nothing bad about this place. The food is outstanding, the service superb, and to top it off, they have delicious gelato.

Stumbled on this place in downtown culver City looking for a quiet place to enjoy a glass of wine and chat with my date. Had a really nice glass of cabernet franc and we were able to sit and chat for a few hours. Really great experience!

Pretty decent but rather ordinary sushi for the most part. Fast service, contemporary atmosphere manages to almost offset the fact that you’re literally next door to Trader Joe’s... and the crazy busy parking structure the two businesses share.

As it is, K-ZO is a slightly more upscale place in both decor and price, where the value is just-decent-enough to feel okay, yet the fish selection isn’t exotic enough to stand out.
Yummy happy hours choices. Always tasty n fresh. Great fast service
Always among the best Japanese restaurants in town. Inovative hot and cold dishes, and some of the best sushi you'll find anywhere.

Had a wonderful meal at K Zo.
The sushi melted in my mouth. Completely clean tasting. Each dish was great. I would love to go back. I chose it based on the reviews. You can't always judge based on likes and ratings. when people shared their experience I knew it was the right place. Super happy.

Really one of the top options for sushi in the West L.A./Culver City area.  It's not inexpensive, but still the ratio of price to quality is amazing.  There is a small bar area if you want to walk in for a drink and some top notch appetizers. But the sushi bar and tables are really where it's at, and for that you would definitely want to reserve ahead of time.  Naturally all of the fish is impeccably sourced and presented by a master crew of sushi chefs. The kitchen menu has plenty to offer as well with outstanding highlights in the age-dashi tofu and salmon skin salad, just to name some personal faves.  Desserts are a hit as well. Guaranteed your entire meal will be artfully presented.  In reality I would expect to pay about 50% more for K-Zo, given the high level of food, service and stylish decor.  Note: do not miss out on the free parking in the connected structure behind the restaurant.
